Bulletin Issued in Brazil to Mark Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- An information bulletin titled "DPRK, country emerging victorious with Songun" was issued by the Brazil-Korea Friendship Association on Aug. 29 on the occasion of the 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK.
 It recalled that President Kim Il Sung fathered the Songun idea as well as the Juche idea after his start of the revolutionary struggle, founded the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and defeated the Japanese imperialists and declared the foundation of the DPRK to the whole world after the liberation of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It pointed to the fact that Kim Il Sung laid down the line of simultaneously building up the economy and defence and the policy of turning the entire army into a cadre army, modernizing the entire army, putting all the people under arms and fortifying the whole country, thereby further augmenting the military muscle of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has developed in depth the Songun idea of Kim Il Sung and put forward the army as a pillar of the country and a main force of the revolution, leading the socialist cause to victory, it noted, adding that the DPRK would win victory under the banner of Songun in the future, too.

Pyongyangites Rejoice over DPRK's Victory at FIFA Women's World Championship 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyangites are very much pleased to hear the news that the DPRK team emerged winner at the FIFA U-20 Women's World Championship.
 Many football fans and people from all walks of life in the DPRK shouted for joy upon hearing the news that the DPRK eleven beat the Chinese team 5:0 in the final on September 3 as they had followed with great expectation and keen interest the championship that began in Moscow on Aug. 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean girls' victory was the topic of the discussion at work places, in families and all other places where people gathered. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Chol, instructor of the Korean Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, had this to say, when interviewed by KCNA: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "I would like to speak highly of our admirable girls as they beat strong teams in Asia, Europe and South America and scored a total of 18 goals in the championship, the biggest points in the history of the FIFA U-20 world women's championship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This victory was possible thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who instilled matchless courage into the footballers and showed boundless love and trust for them while the championship was under way." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Chol Su, a worker of the Pyongyang Thermal Power Complex, said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "I was greatly excited to hear the news that our girls won the world championship. This encouraged us to achieve an unprecedented high boost in the electricity production today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We believe this signal victory represents the spirit of Korea. We workers will step up the building of a great prosperous powerful nation in the same spirit displayed by them".

U.S. Arbitrariness in International Arena Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- The arbitrariness and unilateralism of the United States behaving itself willfully, disregarding the UN Charter and international law, are the main cause of the disturbance of global peace and security and of military clashes, declares Rodong Sinmun Tuesday.
 In a commentary regarding the one-man show and arbitrariness of the United States in the international arena that have left the United Nations powerless and the UN Charter shaken, the analyst says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is none other than the U.S. which observes international law when it deems this in its interests, but resorts to a hard-line policy and military unilateralism when this is unfavorable to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a result of the one-man show, arbitrariness and unilateralism on the part of the United States that the situation of the Korean Peninsula has reached a critical phase on the eve of a war. Its malicious moves to form an encircling ring around the DPRK and military blackmail against it are a wanton violation of the UN Charter which bans hostile acts against the UN member nations and a criminal act weakening the UN authority. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the arbitrary and unilateral policy of the U.S. which has gone beyond control is allowed, international justice cannot be ensured and no country can exercise its legitimate rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The realities today in which the sovereignty of different countries is trodden underfoot and global peace and security are facing a grave threat urgently call upon all the countries to maintain a sharper vigilance against the arbitrary and unilateral policy of the U.S. than ever before. The world peace-loving people should oppose and resolutely shatter it.

Anti-North Smear Campaign of Ultra-Right Forces in S. Korea Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary assails the ultra-right forces in south Korea for becoming evermore undisguised in their anti-north smear campaign.
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some time ago, they made public a "report on the results of the investigation made into those abducted by the north during the June 25 war." It is full of sheer lies such as the baseless claim that the north "abducted" south Koreans in an organized manner during the last war and that most of them were "abducted right after the start of the war." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "report" worked out by the above-said elements and released by a reptile newspaper is a sheer fabrication as it grossly tampered with history and falsified facts. It is nothing but a product of the unpardonable anti-north campaign because it seriously insults the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for "those abducted by the north during the June 25 war" much touted by the ultra-right forces in south Korea, they joined the volunteer army to fight against the U.S. imperialists' aggression and courageously came over to the north in quest of a worthwhile life, after being disillusioned with the colonial fascist rule in force in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through this rash act of making profound confusing of right and wrong the above-said elements seek to stoke extreme bitterness towards the north, zealously pursuant to the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK, in a bid to chill the daily mounting desire to achieve reunification through the pro-north movement and alliance with the north in south Korea and stem the trend of the June 15 era of reunification and restore the outdated era of confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding what the ultra-right conservative forces in south Korea are now doing against the nation as the last-ditch efforts of those forsaken by the era, the commentary urges them not to waste time with peddling the fiction about "those abducted by the north" but probe the truth behind the luring and abduction operation conducted by them in collusion with the U.S. to forcibly take people from the north to the south and open it to the public and make an apology for the crime.

Popular Educational System of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- Twentynine years have elapsed since President Kim Il Sung made public "Theses on Socialist Education" on Sept. 5, 1977.
 On the occasion, the Korean people are looking back on the imperishable exploits performed by the President in the establishment of the most popular educational system and in its consolidation and development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President, who regarded education as a key problem decisive of the rise or fall of the country, saw to it to give preference to founding Kim Il Sung University in the early days of the construction of a new country and to lay a solid base for training native cadres with the university as its matrix. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He let the Provisional People's Committee of North Korea adopt a decision "Regulations on the School Education System of North Korea and the Step to Enforce Them" in December Juche 35 (1946), thus opening a broad avenue for education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even during the hard-fought Korean war decisive to the destiny of the country he directed deep attention to the evacuation of all the universities to safe places so that they would continue educational work. And he took epochal measures unprecedented in history to recall all the teachers, scholars and students from the front and to set up the study-while-working system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the guidance of the President, a decision on carrying the universal compulsory primary education into effect from 1956 was adopted and a law on enforcing the universal compulsory secondary education from Nov. 1, 1958 was promulgated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Free education started in primary schools in 1956 and in middle schools in 1958 and tuition system was abolished in all the schools up to universities and postgraduate courses on April 1, 1959. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's theses marked a new turning point in the development of education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Thanks to the popular educational policy of the President the educational system of the country has been constantly consolidated and developed, the overall education reached incomparably high standard and a compulsory education of high level is being enforced in the country.

Establishment of Fair International Political Order Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- It is necessary to put the earliest possible end to the present unfair international political order whereby human rights standards are applied to certain countries in a selective manner though they should be based on the principle of objectivity and universal value. For the present, the U.S. should be forced to roll back its unreasonable policy to use human rights as a pretext for interfering in the internal affairs of other countries and an important lever for realizing its wild ambition for world supremacy. 
 Minju Joson Tuesday observes this in a signed commentary. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Israel is neither censured nor held accountable for its military actions against innocent civilians because such countries as the U.S. styling itself a "human rights judge" are abusing the human rights issue for attaining their sinister political purposes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. was behind the recent military operation of Israel. It not only supported Israel in its military actions but protected it from international criticism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. can never escape from the responsibility for Israel's crimes against humanity as the U.S. and Israel were closely linked with each other politically over the Lebanese situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This hard fact had an impact on the stand of the U.S. and other Western countries and some international organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is hard reality today that human rights standards vary according to which countries the U.S. deals with.
